  "texts": [
    "To solve a SMFG is to find an optimal policy for the leader, given that the followers best respond.",
    "We define Φ(ϕ) = J l (ϕ, µ ⋆ (ϕ)) for all ϕ and express the objective as followsϕ ⋆ ≜ argmax ϕ∈∆ S B Φ(ϕ) = argmax ϕ∈∆ S B J l (ϕ, µ ⋆ (ϕ)).",
    "(6)3 AlgorithmThe algorithm developed in this work is based on the principle of independent learning.",
    "To motivate our approach, consider a scenario where oracle knowledge is available on µ ⋆ (ϕ) for any ϕ.",
    "In this case, we can optimize ϕ iteratively with gradient descent -we maintain ϕ k (where k is the iteration index) and update ϕ k in the direction of the gradient ∇Φ(ϕ k), which can be evaluated using µ ⋆ (ϕ k).In practice, oracle access to µ ⋆ (ϕ k) is unavailable, and we must solve the lower-level MFG to approximate it."
